While I was waiting for another layer of my mermaid image to render, I walked away and resumed Moon Knight where I'd left off before, when I wasn't yet ready for it. The render took long enough for me to not only finish the series, but make myself something to eat after.

My brain is running really hot right now because I saw so much of my own work lately reflected back at me in that very silly series. The compression algorithms, the using a different name to give myself permission to revisit and re-examine the pains I'd hidden from myself.

It's nice to be able to see myself in things, where I so struggled to before because so much was behind gates and doors and chains and locks. I saw in his path just how far I had to take myself to find myself. My hearts, my dreams, my loves and hopes. How far from them I'd gone.

I'm not plural, of course, but I have been using names and faces to a lot of an extent like Marc did. To find my way back to balance, to forgive myself, to find my way forward. It's all dressed up in Marvel faffenaffery and all, but I still let myself feel the meanings of things.
